<br>
Kinda interesting to read this now, a month or so after PoP is out.<br>
<br>
**************************<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>61: Castigate (8.0 second stun, 420 HP DD, 450 mana, 3.0 cast, 24.0 recast) --- Useless... stun spells are for stunning. I don't want another stun with a bit more damage... i want a faster cast/recast time. Our L5 stun is still my main<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This was released as Tarnation, which I still don't have... but I don't want it. Sound of Might was changed and makes Tarnation useless if you have it. See below! =P<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>61: Ward of Gallantry(+54 AC, 81 min duration, 425 mana)--- Useless, I haven't cast a single-target buff for months, except on random newbies<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, believe it or not, I use this a lot now. Since the combo of druid/shaman/cleric buffs is actually quite a bit better than Virtue, most of my guild uses Nine/Seventh/Kazad instead, so I get quite a few requests for this extra AC buff, since it stacks with the rest.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>61: Symbol of Kazad (850 point symbol, 1 peridot, 600 mana, 63 min duration) --- It's alright, a few casters might want it, if other new PoP buffs of their own don't interfere<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Again, this (or the group version) is normally the buff of choice for us now, so I use this a lot.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>61: Supernal Remedy(1250 Heal, 500 mana, 3.25 casting, 3.5 spell recovery)--- Sure, I'll take it, basically same spell as EthRemedy, a fast heal with a bit of punch<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
PoP is the expansion of fast and furious mobs. So we need every fast heal we can get. This spell is extremely useful. In fact, PoP is *almost* to the point that CH is a thing of the past. It's too slow when you're fighting high-level mobs that QUAD for 2400 (yes, that's right, they're out there, have fun, I kknow I am =P)<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>62: Condemnation(1100 magic based DD, 365 mana, 6.5 cast, 7.0 recast)---Decent damage, but you can only cast it every 15.5 seconds, what's the use? KS group on a raid maybe? /army command will make it obsolete if it ever goes in<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A good nuke upgrade, when we actually use nukes. Spell haste makes it a lot more effective, still wish the recast time was lower.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>62: Supernal Elixir(500 heal over Time, 4 ticks, 450 mana, casting time 4.0)--- 2000hp heal over time, I LIKE this one a lot, especially with the big hp boosts PoP is bringing =)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
With viscious mobs comes viscious heal aggro. When the expansion came out, I used this a lot, but lately I primarily use SR/SL, mostly cuz waiting 6 secs for another tick of healing often isn't enough. Still, very useful for non-dire situations when you want to avoid aggro.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>62: Virtue (+72 AC +1500 hit points, 1 peridot, 1000 mana, 150 mins) --- Nice for a while, but only a placeholder until L65 group version<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Woot! I nailed this one! Except that Virtue is surprisingly under used now that we have other class' hp buffs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>62: Fetter --- *shrug* a root that casts faster, which is nice<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, we never got this, but we got two other roots. The higher level one is ok, holds a while, but 2.0 secs is still quite a while to get a root off when you have 3 mobs beating on you =)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>63: Sound of Might (5.0 second AE stun, 75 mana, 0.75 casting. 30.0 second recast) --- Good for AoE groups, nothing else... and I almost never AoE<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This was changed to a single-target spell with a 0.8 cast time. It lands on mobs up to (63? 65?). Excellent spell. I actually unmem DB to have room for this now. A powerful stun that gives me enough time to back away and root.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>63: Hammer of Damnation (another hammer proccer!) --- No opinion until I see the stats/procs etc<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ok, it's better than L60 version, but the whole idea of battle cleric is mostly only for fun. I only pull out the hammer if I'm really bored or we're in an easy camp. Now if only this spell was castable ON our weapons instead of summoned... =P<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>63: Armor of the Zealot (36 AC, 450 hp, 8mana/tick regen self only buff, 400 mana, 144 min duration) --- Upgrade to one of my favorite spells =)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Changed to L65, I don't have yet. BUT at this point, I really don't think I'll use it when I get it, at least on raids. The buff combo gives better hp and the mana regen is just as good. It'll be very nice for xp groups though.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>63: Catastrophe ( 850 point magic based Poitn Blank AE nuke, 650 mana, 5.0 casting 24.0 recast) --- *shrug* the few times I've AoE'd, I rarely CAST AE, I'm busy healing. 90% useless<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
/shrug, it's a good AE spell, which I personally have no use for... maybe cast it once a month hehe<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>64: Word of Reviviscence (AE rez, not quite done yet, 1100 mana) --- Personally, I don't think this is a rez spell. I look at it as the same situation as the Restoration/Word of Restoration spells we already have... one is a rez, the other is a group heal. Just a similarity in naming. A couple of my reasons atm, based on the current stats of the spell: If it's an AE rez, it would be one of the absolute best spells in the game. It should be L65 and cost a LOT more than 1100 mana, maybe like 3-4k mana. I think it's an AE heal that still VI is still tweaking. Just my current opinion =)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A-HA! I was right! Not a rez! =P This was changed, it's a group/AE heal, although I don't have it yet. Extremely useful in the PoP raid environment.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>64: Mark of Kings (9 point healing mark on target, 170 mana, 3.0 second casting 3.5 min duration) --- Ok, though the way MoK works right now makes me rarely use it... only on boss mob fights. The heal component is negligible except over long periods of time. In groups, only real use is to remove mob DS. Plus, the current version is highly resistable.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It's definitely better than MoKarn. I use it more, but still not that great a spell. Good for boss mobs, maybe xp groups if it's easy and you don't have to watch your mana closely.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>64: Destroy Undead( 1200 undead-only nuke, 300 mana, 5.0 casting) --- Excellent spell, damage/mana ration kicks ass... however, there's a severe lack of undead zones/camps in the game. Unless PoP has more, soloing with this spell will still be based on your luck getting a camp to use it in.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Don't have it yet, but the same thing applies. PoP undead mobs generally hit MUCH too hard to solo, so it's another spell with (unfortunately) little practical use.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>65: Supernal Light (2200 hp heal, 690 mana, 5.2 casting) --- *shrug* The amount healed is nice, but the only situations I'd want a fast, mana-inefficient heal like this, I want cast speed over amount healed. I'd almost always use Supernal Remedy over this, same as Eth Rem completely took over for DL.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ok, this and SupRem are my two main heals now, even replacing CH. It's still kinda mana-inefficient, but it heals 2750hp in 2.8 secs if you have some spell haste. I can get 3 of these off the same time it takes to CH a single person. New game environment makes this highly useful. Was changed to L63 too<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>65: Hand of Virtue( group Virtue, 2 peridots, 2500 mana, 150 mins) --- Will be our bread and butter buff, nuff said.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It's good to have, but as I've said before, the majority of my guild prefers Nine/Seven/Kazad.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>65: Mark of the Righteous ( reverse damange shield of 41, 200 mana, 3.0 cast, 3.0 recast) --- Amazing spell, almost three times our current MoR.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Awesome spell, I was lucky enough to get the first (and so far only) copy on the server. Did I mention it's an awesome spell? =P<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>65: The Silent Command (blinds, stuns for 3.0 seconds, 700 damage point blank AE, 550 mana, 1.0 casting, 120.0 recast) --- What's the point? Yet another extremely situational spell<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Still mostly useless, though I don't have yet.<br>
